          <td style="width: 75%" class="auto-style1">This is a four hour course which is intended to provide first responders with necessary knowledge when dealing with emergent operations on or about the railroad. It will utilize a combination of power point and Railroad and FEMA produced DVD videos to educate and re-enforce the dos and don’ts of working on railroad property. It will also provide information on safety and override features of common railroad locomotives and light rail equipment. This course is intended for any emergency responder who may be required to enter upon rail road right of ways or property during the course of their day to day duties. </td> 
