         </tr> 
         <tr> 
          <td style="width: 25%" class="auto-style1" valign="top"><strong>CONTENT</strong></td> 
          <td style="width: 75%" class="auto-style1"> This program will review the fundamental management functions of the Command Staff responsibilities using table top activities that will enhance the knowledge of the class. Students will get to develop the Incident Action Plan (IAPs), the components of planning, and how to conduct a planning meeting. Emphasis on how to integrate the operational period brief and the tactical brief with utilizing the Incident Support Team (IST) concepts is standard information each student will accomplish through this exercise. </td> 
         </tr> 
         <tr> 
          <td style="width: 25%" class="auto-style1" valign="top"><strong>REQUIREMENT(S)</strong></td> 
          <td style="width: 75%" class="auto-style1"> </td> 
         </tr> 
         <tr> 
          <td style="width: 25%" class="auto-style1" valign="top"><strong>PRE-REQUISITE</strong></td> 
          <td style="width: 75%" class="auto-style1">Any Officer; Supervisor; Command Staff; Unit Leader; Task Force/Strike Team Leader</td> 
         </tr> 
        </tbody>
       </table> 
       <br> 
